reviewText: When I watch these, my heart is heavy. Little Beaver has grown up and part of him wants to go back and be a little boy. But he can't, neither can we. The producers did an exceptional job portraying all of these mixed emotions in the final season. Cudos to the writers, to the cast as well.This was the most realistic show of it's time about boyhood. Yes, boys were once like this and parents were once like this.

reviewText: I haven't seen this dvd set yet, but after viewing some of the other Shout releases of this terrific show, I doubt that I'm going to be disappointed!!  I'm so excited that I'll be able to complete my Beaver collection this March.  I have been waiting for years for this day to come, and I know countless others are just as happy as I am going to be!  Thank you in advance Shout for releasing the rest of "Leave it to Beaver" on dvd for the many of us who love this show because of its simplicity, yet classic and honest humor and lessons in life.  This show takes us back to the days when life was more than just playing video games, talking on cell phones, touching ipads, watching reality tv, and reading kindles.  Families shared their joys, pains, triumphs, and struggles in day-to-day living through talks at the dinner table, breakfast time, or at school or out playing.  I only wish more people would take the time to enjoy their daily lives like they did back in the Beaver days.  Now, we're too consumed with the internet, Wii, & blu ray sets that family life sadly comes last most of the time, and our lives are quickly passing us by not giving us time to enjoy even the simplest things in life.  If you feel like your life is just moving too quickly and you would like to savor those "special" little moments, please take a few minutes to sit down and watch a few episodes of "Leave it to Beaver" where you can relax and remember what life really is all about.

reviewText: I love this set.  I can't think of any other shows that had this kind of "staying power" through the final season.  No matter how many times I watch them, I still laugh.  Everyone is older now, true, but Ken Osmond has perfected his role as mischievous Eddie Haskell, Tony Dow is content to be the big brother, and Ward and June continue to be the parents we all wish we had. The writers continue to come up with interesting episodes and situations ("messes") for the gang to get themselves into and out of.  Don't miss buying this final set to complete your collection.

reviewText: The sixth season of Leave It To Beaver aired from 1962 to 1963. This set has all 39 uncut and remastered episodes spread out over 6 single-sided dual-layered dvds.The episodes on this set are:Disc One:01. Wally's Dinner Date02. Beaver's Football Award03. Wally's License04. The Late Edition05. Double Date06. Eddie, The Businessman07. Tell It To EllaDisc Two:08. Bachelor At Large09. Beaver Joins A Record Club10. Wally's Car Accident11. Beaver, The Sheep Dog12. Beaver, The Hero13. Beaver's AutobiographyDisc Three:14. The Party Spoiler15. The Mustache16. Wally Buys A Car17. The Parking Attendants18. More Blessed To Give19. Beaver's Good Deed20. The Credit CardDisc Four:21. Beaver the Caddy22. Beaver On TV23. Box Office Attraction24. Lumpy's Scholarship25. The Silent Treatment26. Uncle Billy's VisitDisc Five:27. Beaver's Prep School28. Wally and the Fraternity29. Eddie's Sweater30. The Book Report31. The Poor Loser32. Don Juan Beaver33. Summer In AlaskaDisc Six:34. Beaver's Graduation35. Wally's Practical Joke36. The All Night Party37. Beaver Sees America38. The Clothing Drive39. Family ScrapbookVideo: Shout Factory went all-out and did an incredible job remastering Leave It To Beaver. The show is presented in its original full frame 1:33 ratio and looks fantastic. The show is in black & white and looks clean, sharp, and bright.Audio: The only audio track on this set is English 2.0 mono. It is clear sounding and I have no complaintsSubtitles: There are no subtitles on the set but it is close-captioned in English only.
summary: I'm not just giving you the business Sam, this is one swell dvd set
